resource.chars: There is a young man-- not so old-- about middle- aged — who is stout, and
fat. His blouse is overhanging. He walks straight with his head up. He has
eyeglasses on, and always wears a dark suit. He is always joking about what
he sees in you that is funny, and he always likes to talk about girls, for he is
a bachelor. He seems to be full of energy in his work cobbling your sole;
not the soul that is within you, but the one you put your hoof into.
He is a cobbler; a good one too.
He is about 54 inches high. Wears dark glasses and slick. Usually wears
a brown sweater. Hates à necktie and never wears one. Always talking.
Never still except when he is asleep in a class. He comes out in weekly
Sara Poncho: " Why is that referee looking under those fellows who
are lying on the mat. Has he lost something?"
Some Senior boys go to socials for the lower classes?
So many girls crowd to the doos when school is dismissed?
The Senior girls brought hcme so much extra amole root?
So many boys take auto- mechanics?
Girls like to give" senior dinners? "
The bandstand is such a popular prcmenade?
Menaul boys always occupy the auditorium steps on Sundays.
So many girls like to work in the kitchen?
Sara Poncho would like to study French?
Some girls like to work at the greenhouse?
Walter Juan doesn' t jar loose and treat some of the girls?
The Filling Station is so popular on Sundays?
Dining room girls wear black hose?
